Each county advisory committee and intercounty advisory committee shall:
Monitor, review and evaluate the allocation and adequacy of publicly funded mental health services within the county through means such as conducting or participating in site visits;
Determine the needs of the county mental health system, including quality of services, gaps in the system, and interagency coordination;
Participate in the development of the local mental health plan and local mental health budget;
Prepare and disseminate an annual report to the following:
The health officer;
In Montgomery County, the director of the Montgomery County Department of Health and Human Services;
The county mental health director;
The governing body of the appropriate county;
The director of the local core service agency, if any;
The regional mental health director;
The Director;
The Secretary; and
The Maryland Advisory Council on Mental Hygiene; and
Include in the annual report, at a minimum, the following:
A description of the progress of the county mental health system;
Recommendations on actions needed to improve the system;
Recommendations on priorities for allocation of funds; and
In accordance with those priorities and after consideration of financial resources, recommendations on appropriate allocation of funds;
Review and comment upon the annual core service agency or county mental health plan and preliminary budget, prior to submission of the budget to the State; and
Review and comment upon the annual fiscal report.
